<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-26T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Lane, Clayton/118: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">William Phillips</persName>, Personal
                                Representative of President <persName>Roosevelt</persName> in
                                India</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-26T21:00:00-04:00">April 26,
                                    1943—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. Your 288, April 16, 2 p.m. Lane’s designation as Commercial Attaché
                            canceled.</p>
                        <p>In lieu thereof, he is designated Secretary with the additional title of
                            Director of War Economic Operations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>